Your results show the relative strength: Your results show the relative strength of different intelligence types. Dominant intelligence types indicate your natural inclinations and abilities. Remember that all intelligence types are important and can be developed.
Linguistic Intelligence Description: The ability to effectively use words and language. People with developed linguistic intelligence express their thoughts well orally and in writing.
Logical-Mathematical Intelligence Descri: The ability to effectively use numbers and reason logically. Includes sensitivity to logical patterns and relationships.
Spatial Intelligence Description: The ability to perceive the visual-spatial world and transform visual-spatial representations.
Musical Intelligence Description: The ability to perceive, distinguish, transform, and express musical forms.
Bodily-Kinesthetic Intelligence Descript: The ability to use the whole body or parts of it to solve problems or create products.
Intrapersonal Intelligence Description: The ability to understand oneself, one's feelings, fears, and motivations.
Interpersonal Intelligence Description: The ability to perceive and distinguish moods, intentions, motivations, and feelings of other people.
Naturalistic Intelligence Description: The ability to recognize and classify various types of flora and fauna in the environment.
Existential Intelligence Description: The ability to reflect on fundamental questions of human existence, the meaning of life, spirituality, and philosophical concepts.
